HEADWORD: Reconstruct
<hw>Re`con*struct"</hw> <pr>(-str?kt")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To
construct again; to rebuild; to remodel; to form again or
anew.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Regiments had been dissolved and <qex>reconstructed</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reconstruction</ent>⟦br⟧
